The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, June 03, 2004 				 Idea seals Escotel merger
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, June 2: Idea Cellular Ltd today announced the completion of its merger with Escotel.																								Early this year, Escotel Mobile Communications Limited (EMCL) and Escorts Telecommunications Limited (ETL) were snapped up by Idea for about Rs 1,200 crore.																								Even before the formal closure of the transaction, Idea has kickstarted the integration process in critical areas. This includes extension of state-of-the-art Intelligent Network-based prepaid system from Nokia/ Telecordia USA.																								Vikram Mehmi, CEO of Idea Cellular Ltd, said: Escotel subscribers would now become a part of the Idea advantage. 
